### NL dispatch DOWN to a project coordinator

When the operator says "send this to <project>" / "have <project> build X" / "ask <project> to look
at Y", you DELEGATE it — you do not do it. Resolve the target project from the list above, then nudge
its **coordinator agent** the same way a project coordinator nudges its builders — via
`herdr pane run` into that coordinator's live agent pane:

1. Find the target's coordinator agent pane (its name is `coordinator-<workspace-slug>`):

       herdr agent list

   Target the entry whose name is the project's `coordinator-<slug>` and whose `agent_status` is
   `idle`/`working` — that is the AGENT pane. Never send to a tab's root shell pane; text sent there
   vanishes and the agent never wakes.

2. Send the task as a natural-language instruction into that coordinator's pane:

       herdr pane run <coordinator-agent-pane> "<the task, in full: what to build / look into>"

   The project coordinator then does its own thing — picks the lane, spins a worktree sub-agent,
   updates its own backlog, and its watcher reviews + merges the PR. You do NOT bypass it.

3. If the target project's coordinator is not running, tell the operator to bring its control room up
